Thales the Father of the Ionick Sect, held (as Laertius tells us) that Water was the Principle of all things, and that the World was animated [
   〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
] In which Doctrines (as is very probable) he was instructed by the Mosaick Tradition [of the Waters, and the Spirit that moved upon them] for unto this his Dogmata are very conformable.
